'''Abdullah Abdulrahman Al-Hamdan''' ({{langx|ar|عَبْد الله عَبْد الرَّحْمٰن الْحَمْدَان}}; born 12 September 1999) is a Saudi Arabian football player who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Saudi Pro League]] club [[Al-Nassr FC|Al-Nassr]] and the [[Saudi Arabia national football team|Saudi Arabia national team]].

He is the son of former [[Al Shabab Club|Al-Shabab]] goalkeeper and former [[Hetten FC|Hetten]] manager, Abdulrahman Al-Hamdan. Al-Hamdan studied at Riyadh Schools and joined the [[Al Shabab Club|Al-Shabab]] academy at an early age, where he developed his talent to become one of the top rising Saudi talents. After a period with [[Al-Hilal SFC|Al-Hilal]], he officially moved to [[Al-Nassr FC|Al-Nassr]] on 2 February 2026.<ref name="almodrj">{{cite web |title=Al-Nassr signs Al-Hamdan and dispenses with Camara |url=https://almodrj.com/archives/25164 |publisher=Al-Modrj |accessdate=4 February 2026 |language=Arabic }}</ref>

<ref name="kooora">{{cite web |title=Abdullah Al-Hamdan |url=https://www.kooora.com/?player=68362= |accessdate=11 October 2019 }}{{Dead link|date=August 2025 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>

==Club career==
Al-Hamdan is an academy graduate of Al-Shabab. In 2018, as part of a deal between the [[Saudi Arabian Football Federation]] and [[La Liga]], Al-Hamdan joined Spanish club [[Sporting de Gijón|Sporting Gijón]]'s [[Sporting de Gijón (youth)|U19 squad]] on a six-month loan.<ref>{{cite web |title=El Sporting incorpora a la base al juvenil saudí Abdullah Al Hamdan |url=https://www.elcomercio.es/sporting/sporting-incorpora-base-20180122001053-ntvo.html}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Abdullah Al Hamdan despunta como goleador en el Sporting |url=https://www.lavozdeasturias.es/noticia/sporting1905/2018/03/28/abdullah-hamdan-despunta-goleador-sporting/00031522255143908672722.htm}}</ref> He returned to Al-Shabab following the conclusion of the 2017–18 season.

On 2 January 2019, Al-Hamdan made his debut with the first team in the [[2019 King Cup|King Cup]] match against [[Al-Sahel FC|Al-Sahel]] coming off the bench in the 61st minute to replace [[Khalid Kaabi]].<ref>{{cite web |title=التبديل الثاني|url=https://twitter.com/AlShababSaudiFC/status/1080458691302879233}}</ref> Al-Hamdan made his league debut in the match against [[Al-Wehda Club (Mecca)|Al-Wehda]] on 15 February 2019.<ref>{{cite web |title=سوماديكا يضم الحمدان وتمبكتي لقائمة الفريق الأول |url=https://www.dawriplus.com/news/34809-%D8%B3%D9%88%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%8A%D9%83%D8%A7-%D9%8A%D8%B6%D9%85-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AD%D9%85%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%86-%D9%88%D8%AA%D9%85%D8%A8%D9%83%D8%AA%D9%8A-%D9%84%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%A6%D9%85%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%81%D8%B1%D9%8A%D9%82-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D9%88%D9%84.html}}</ref> He made his first start for the club in the final match of the 2018–19 season against [[Al Hilal SFC|Al-Hilal]].<ref>{{cite web |title=AL HILAL VS. AL SHABAB  3 - 2 |url=https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2019/05/16/saudi-arabia/pro-league/al-hilal-riyadh/al-shabab-riyadh/2830537/}}</ref> On 23 September 2019, Al-Hamdan scored his first goal for the club in the [[Arab Club Champions Cup]] match against Algerian club [[JS Saoura]], he also assisted [[Danilo Moreno Asprilla|Danilo Asprilla]]'s goal to put Al-Shabab 3–1 ahead.<ref>{{cite web |title=مباراة شبيبة الساورة الشباب |url=https://www.filgoal.com/matches/258357/coverage/%D9%85%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%A9-%D8%B4%D8%A8%D9%8A%D8%A8%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B3%D8%A7%D9%88%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B4%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%A8-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D9%83%D8%A3%D8%B3-%D9%85%D8%AD%D9%85%D8%AF-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B3%D8%A7%D8%AF%D8%B3-%D9%84%D9%84%D8%A3%D9%86%D8%AF%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%A8%D8%B7%D8%A7%D9%84}}</ref> Four days later, Al-Hamdan scored his first league goal in the 2–1 loss against [[Al-Ittihad Club (Jeddah)|Al-Ittihad]].<ref>{{cite web |title=AL SHABAB VS. AL ITTIHAD  1 - 2 |url=https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2019/09/27/saudi-arabia/pro-league/al-shabab-riyadh/al-ittihad-jeddah/3102168/}}</ref> He ended his second season at the club scoring 5 goals in 22 appearances in all competitions.

On 7 November 2020, Al-Hamdan came off the bench in the 94th minute and assisted [[Turki Al-Ammar]]'s third goal in the 3–1 away win against [[Al-Fateh SC|Al-Fateh]].<ref>{{cite web |title=AL FATEH VS. AL SHABAB  1 - 3|url=https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2020/11/07/saudi-arabia/pro-league/al-fath-alahsa/al-shabab-riyadh/3400414/}}</ref> On 23 November 2020, Al-Hamdan made his first start of the season and assisted [[Cristian Guanca]]'s equalizer in the 2–2 draw against [[Al-Ahli Saudi FC|Al-Ahli]].<ref>{{cite web |title=AL AHLI VS. AL SHABAB  2 - 2 |url=https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2020/11/23/saudi-arabia/pro-league/al-ahli-jeddah/al-shabab-riyadh/3400418/}}</ref> On 27 November 2020, Al-Hamdan came off the bench and assisted Turki Al-Ammar's winner in the 2–1 win against [[Damac FC|Damac]].<ref>{{cite web |title=AL SHABAB VS. DAMAK  2 - 1 |url=https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2020/11/27/saudi-arabia/pro-league/al-shabab-riyadh/dhamk/3400425/}}</ref> On 2 December 2020, he assisted Cristian Guanca's equalizer in the 2–2 draw against Al-Ittihad in the first leg of the [[Arab Club Champions Cup]] semi-finals. On 26 December 2020, Al-Hamdan started the league match against [[Al-Batin FC|Al-Batin]] and assisted two goals.<ref>{{cite web |title=AL SHABAB VS. AL BATIN  3 - 1 |url=https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2020/12/26/saudi-arabia/pro-league/al-shabab-riyadh/al-baten/3400462/}}</ref> On 14 January 2021, Al-Hamdan scored his first goal of the season in the 3–0 away win against [[Al-Ain FC (Saudi Arabia)|Al-Ain]], he also assisted Cristian Guanca's opener.<ref>{{cite web |title=AL-AIN VS. AL SHABAB  0 - 3 |url=https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2021/01/14/saudi-arabia/pro-league/saudi-arabia-al-ain-fc/al-shabab-riyadh/3400483/}}</ref> On 19 January 2021, he assisted [[Fábio Martins]]'s equalizer in the 1–1 draw against [[Al-Faisaly FC|Al-Faisaly]].<ref>{{cite web |title=AL SHABAB VS. AL FAISALY  1 - 1 |url=https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2021/01/19/saudi-arabia/pro-league/al-shabab-riyadh/al-faysaly-al-majmaah/3400492/}}</ref> On 25 January 2021, Al-Hamdan scored once and assisted once in the 4–2 away win against Al-Wehda.<ref>{{cite web |title=AL WAHDA VS. AL SHABAB  2 - 4 |url=https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2021/01/25/saudi-arabia/pro-league/al-wehda-mecca/al-shabab-riyadh/3400502/}}</ref> On 6 February 2021, Al-Hamdan made his final appearance for Al-Shabab in the 4–1 home win against [[Al-Raed FC|Al-Raed]]. He left the pitch in tears while being replaced by [[Odion Ighalo]] in the 84th minute.<ref>{{cite web |title=بالدموع.. عبدالله الحمدان يودع زملاءه في الشباب|url=https://arabic.sport360.com/article/football/%D9%83%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D8%B3%D8%B9%D9%88%D8%AF%D9%8A%D8%A9/1032049/%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AF%D9%85%D9%88%D8%B9-%D8%B9%D8%A8%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%84%D9%87-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AD%D9%85%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%86-%D9%8A%D9%88%D8%AF%D8%B9-%D8%B2%D9%85%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%A1%D9%87-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B4%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%A8-%D9%81%D9%8A%D8%AF%D9%8A%D9%88}}</ref> He made 51 appearances for Al-Shabab in all competitions and scored 7 goals and recorded 12 assists.

On 6 February 2021, Al-Hamdan joined [[Al Hilal SFC|Al-Hilal]] on a five-year contract for a reported fee of [[Saudi riyal|SAR]]3 million.<ref>{{cite web |title=الهلال يعلن شراء المدة المتبقية من عقد الحمدان |url=https://www.alarabiya.net/sport/2021/02/07/%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%87%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%84-%D9%8A%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%86-%D8%B4%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%A1-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%AF%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%AA%D8%A8%D9%82%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D9%85%D9%86-%D8%B9%D9%82%D8%AF-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AD%D9%85%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%86}}</ref>

On 3 February 2026, Al-Hamdan joined [[Al-Nassr FC|Al-Nassr]] on a free transfer.<ref>{{cite web |title=رسمياً.. النصر يضم عبدالله الحمدان|url=https://www.okaz.com.sa/sport/na/2234017}}</ref>

==International career==
Al-Hamdan made his debut for the [[Saudi Arabia national football team|Saudi national team]] in a friendly against [[Mali national football team|Mali]] on 5 September 2019.<ref>{{cite web |title=ودية مالي تقود الحمدان لهجوم الأخضر |url=https://www.okaz.com.sa/article/1745492}}</ref> A month later, on 10 October, he scored his first international goal in a 3–0 victory over [[Singapore national football team|Singapore]] during the [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification – AFC second round|2022 FIFA World Cup qualification]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://stats.the-afc.com/match_report/16209 |title=Saudi Arabia 3–0 Singapore |publisher=AFC |date=10 October 2024 }}</ref>

On 28 December 2024, he scored his first brace for his country in a 3–1 victory over [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]] in the [[26th Arabian Gulf Cup]], qualifying his nation to the semi-finals of the competition.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://sportstar.thehindu.com/football/saudi-arabia-beats-iraq-3-1-knocks-defending-champion-out-in-arabian-gulf-cup-2024-semifinal-irq-vs-ksa/article69037901.ece |title=Arabian Gulf Cup 2024: Renard’s Saudi Arabia knocks out defending champion Iraq, wins semifinal 3-1 |publisher=Sportstar |date=28 December 2024 }}</ref>

